President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has amended the disaster declaration for the State of New Mexico, providing additional assistance in response to wildfires and straight-line winds that occurred starting on April 5, 2022. The President has authorized an increase in federal funding for debris removal and emergency protective measures, including direct federal assistance. The federal share of eligible costs has been raised to 100% for a 90-day period from the declaration date. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.